\par LICH
\par }{\fs20 A lich is an undead spellcaster, usually a wizard or sorcerer but sometimes a cleric or other spellcaster, who has used its magical powers to unnaturally extend its life.
\par A lich is a gaunt and skeletal humanoid with withered flesh stretched tight across horribly visible bones. Its eyes have long ago been lost to decay, but bright pinpoints of crimson light burn on in the empty sockets.
\par Liches speak Common plus any other languages they knew in life.
\par 
\par }{CREATING A LICH
\par }{\fs20 \'93Lich\'94 is an acquired template that can be added to any humanoid creature (referred to hereafter as the base creature), provided it can create the required phylactery; see The Lich\rquote s Phylactery, below.
\par A lich has all the base creature\rquote s statistics and special abilities except as noted here.
\par }{\b\fs20 Size and Type:}{\fs20  The creature\rquote s type changes to undead. Do not recalculate base attack bonus, saves, or skill points. Size is unchanged.
\par }{\b\fs20 Hit Dice: }{\fs20 Increase all current and future Hit Dice to d12s.
\par }{\b\fs20 Armor Class:}{\fs20  A lich has a +5 natural armor bonus or the base creature\rquote s natural armor bonus, whichever is better.
\par }{\b\fs20 Attack: }{\fs20 A lich has a touch attack that it can use once per round. If the base creature can use weapons, the lich retains this ability. A creature with natura
l weapons retains those natural weapons. A lich fighting without weapons uses either its touch attack or its primary natural weapon (if it has any). A lich armed with a weapon uses its touch or a weapon, as it desires.
\par }{\b\fs20 Full Attack:}{\fs20  A lich fighting without 
weapons uses either its touch attack (see above) or its natural weapons (if it has any). If armed with a weapon, it usually uses the weapon as its primary attack along with a touch as a natural secondary attack, provided it has a way to make that attack (
either a free hand or a natural weapon that it can use as a secondary attack).
\par }{\b\fs20 Damage:}{\fs20  A lich without natural weapons has a touch attack that uses negative energy to deal 1d8+5 points of damage to living creatures; a Will save (DC 10 + 1/2 lich\rquote s HD + lich\rquote 
s Cha modifier) halves the damage. A lich with natural weapons can use its touch attack or its natural weaponry, as it prefers. If it chooses the latter, it deals 1d8+5 points of extra damage on one natural weapon attack.
\par }{\b\fs20 Special Attacks:}{\fs20  A lich retains all the base creature\rquote s special attacks and gains those described below. Save DCs are equal to 10 + 1/2 lich\rquote s HD + lich\rquote s Cha modifier unless otherwise noted.
\par }{\i\fs20 Fear Aura (Su): }{\fs20 Liches are shrouded in a dreadful aura of death and evil. Creatures of less than 5 HD in a 60-foot radius that look at the lich must succeed on a Will save or be affected as though by a }{\i\fs20 fear }{\fs20 
spell from a sorcerer of the lich\rquote s level. A creature that successfully saves cannot be affected again by the same lich\rquote s aura for 24 hours.
