\par CREATING A LYCANTHROPE
\par }{\fs20 \'93Lycanthrope\'94 is a template that can be added to any humanoid or giant (referred to h
ereafter as the base creature). The lycanthrope template can be inherited (for natural lycanthropes) or acquired (for afflicted lycanthropes). Becoming a lycanthrope is very much like multiclassing as an animal and gaining the appropriate Hit Dice.
\par }{\b\fs20 Size and Type:}{\fs20  The base creature\rquote 
s type does not change, but the creature gains the shapechanger subtype. The lycanthrope takes on the characteristics of some type of carnivorous or omnivorous creature of the animal type (referred to hereafter as the base animal).
\par This animal can be any predator, scavenger, or omnivore whose size is within one size category of the base creature\rquote 
s size (Small, Medium, or Large for a Medium base creature). Lycanthropes can also adopt a hybrid shape that combines features of the base creature and the base animal. A lycanthrope\rquote 
s hybrid form is the same size as the base animal or the base creature, whichever is larger.
\par A lycanthrope uses either the base creature\rquote s or the base animal\rquote s statistics and special abilities in addition to those described here.
\par }{\b\fs20 Hit Dice and Hit Points:}{\fs20  Same as the base creature plus those of the base animal. To calculate total hit points, apply Constitution modifiers according to the score the lycanthrope has in each form. 
\par }{\b\fs20 Speed:}{\fs20  Same as the base creature or base animal, depending on which form the lycanthrope is using. Hybrids use the base creature\rquote s speed.
\par }{\b\fs20 Armor Class:}{\fs20  The base creature\rquote s natural armor bonus increases by +2 in all forms. In hybrid form, the lycanthrope\rquote s natural armor bonus is equal to the na
tural armor bonus of the base animal or the base creature, whichever is better.
\par }{\b\fs20 Base Attack/Grapple:}{\fs20  Add the base attack bonus for the base animal to the base attack bonus for the base creature. The lycanthrope\rquote s grapple bonus uses its attack bonus and mod
ifiers for Strength and size depending on the lycanthrope\rquote s form.
\par }{\b\fs20 Attacks: }{\fs20 Same as the base creature or base animal, depending on which form the lycanthrope is using. A lycanthrope in hybrid form gains two claw attacks and a bite attack as natural weapons.
\par These weapons deal damage based on the hybrid form\rquote s size. A hybrid may attack with a weapon and a bite, or may attack with its natural weapons. The bite attack of a hybrid is a secondary attack.
