\par }{\b\fs20 Special Attacks:}{\fs20  A lycanthrope retains the special attacks of the base creature or base animal, depending on which form it is using, and also gains the special attacks described below.
\par A lycanthrope\rquote s hybrid form does not gain any special attacks of the base animal. A lycanthrope spellcaster cannot cast spells with verbal, somatic, or material components while in animal form, or spells with verbal components while in hybrid form.

\par }{\b\i\fs20 Curse of Lycanthropy (Su):}{\i\fs20  }{\fs20 Any humanoid or giant hit by a natural lycanthrope\rquote s bite attack in animal or hybrid form must succeed on a DC 15 Fortitude save or contract lycanthropy. If the victim\rquote 
s size is not within one size category of the lycanthrope the victim cannot contract lycanthropy from that lycanthrope. Afflicted lycanthropes cannot pass on the curse of lycanthropy.
\par }{\b\fs20 Special Qualities:}{\fs20  A lycanthrope retains all the special qualities of the base creature and the base animal, and also gains those described below.
\par }{\b\i\fs20 Alternate Form (Su):}{\i\fs20  }{\fs20 A lycanthrope can shift into animal form as though using the }{\i\fs20 polymorph }{\fs20 spell on itself, though its gear is not affected, it does not regain hit points for changing form, and only
 the specific animal form indicated for the lycanthrope can be assumed. It does not assume the ability scores of the animal, but instead adds the animal\rquote 
s physical ability score modifiers to its own ability scores. A lycanthrope also can assume a bipedal hybrid form with prehensile hands and animalistic features.
\par Changing to or from animal or hybrid form is a standard action.
\par A slain lycanthrope reverts to its humanoid form, although it remains dead. Separated body parts retain their animal form, however.
\par Afflicted lycanthropes find this ability difficult to control (see Lycanthropy as an Affliction, below), but natural lycanthropes have full control over this power.
\par }{\b\i\fs20 Damage Reduction (Ex): }{\fs20 An afflicted lycanthrope in animal or hybrid form has damage reduction 5/silver. A natural lycanthrope in animal or hybrid form has damage reduction 10/silver.
\par }{\b\i\fs20 Lycanthropic Empathy (Ex):}{\i\fs20  }{\fs20 In any form, lycanthropes can communicate and empathize with normal or dire animals of their animal form. This gives them a +4 racial bonus on checks when influencing the animal\rquote 
s attitude and allows the communication of simple concepts and (if the animal is friendly) commands, such as \'93friend,\'94 \'93foe,\'94 \'93flee,\'94 and \'93attack.\'94
\par }{\b\i\fs20 Low-Light Vision (Ex): }{\fs20 A lycanthrope has low-light vision in any form.
\par }{\b\i\fs20 Scent (Ex): }{\fs20 A lycanthrope has the scent ability in any form. 
\par }{\b\fs20 Base Save Bonuses:}{\fs20  Add the base save bonuses of the base animal to the base save bonuses of the base creature.
\par }{\b\fs20 Abilities:}{\fs20  All lycanthropes gain +2 to Wisdom. In addition, when in animal form, a lycanthrope\rquote s physical ability scores improve according to its kind, as set out in the table below. These adjustments are equal to the animal
\rquote s normal ability scores \endash 10 or \endash 11. A lycanthrope in hybrid form modifies its physical ability scores by the same amount.
\par In addition, a lycanthrope may also gain an additional ability score increase by virtue of its extra Hit Dice.
\par }{\b\fs20 Skills:}{\fs20  A lycanthrope gains skill points equal to (2 + Int modifier, minimum 1) per Hit Die of its animal form, as if it had multiclas
sed into the animal type. (Animal is never its first Hit Die, though, and it does not gain quadruple skill points for any animal Hit Die.) Any skill given in the animal\rquote s description is a class skill for the lycanthrope\rquote 
s animal levels. In any form, a lycanthrope also has any racial skill bonuses of the base creature and of the base animal, although conditional skill bonuses only apply in the associated form.
