\par LYCANTHROPY AS AN AFFLICTION
\par }{\fs20 When a character contracts lycanthropy through a lycanthrope\rquote 
s bite (see above), no symptoms appear until the first night of the next full moon. On that night, the afflicted character involuntarily assumes animal form and forgets his or her own identity, temporarily becoming an NPC. The cha
racter remains in animal form, assuming the appropriate alignment, until the next dawn.
\par The character\rquote s actions during this first episode are dictated by the alignment of its animal form. The character remembers nothing about the entire episode (or subsequ
ent episodes) unless he succeeds on a DC 15 Wisdom check, in which case he becomes aware of his lycanthropic condition.
\par Thereafter, the character is subject to involuntary transformation under the full moon and whenever damaged in combat. He or she feels a
n overwhelming rage building up and must succeed on a Control Shape check (see below) to resist changing into animal form. Any player character not yet aware of his or her lycanthropic condition temporarily becomes an NPC during an involuntary change, and
 acts according to the alignment of his or her animal form.
\par A character with awareness of his condition retains his identity and does not lose control of his actions if he changes. However, each time he changes to his animal form, he must make a Will save (
DC 15 + number of times he has been in animal form) or permanently assume the alignment of his animal form in all shapes. 
\par Once a character becomes aware of his affliction, he can now voluntarily attempt to change to animal or hybrid form, using the approp
riate Control Shape check DC. An attempt is a standard action and can be made each round. Any voluntary change to animal or hybrid form immediately and permanently changes the character\rquote s alignment to that of the appropriate lycanthrope.
\par }{\fs22 
\par Changing Form
\par }{\fs20 Changing form is a standard action. If the change is involuntary, the character performs the change on his next turn following the triggering event. Changing to animal or hybrid form ruins the character\rquote 
s armor and clothing (including any items worn) if the new form is larger than the character\rquote 
s natural form; carried items are simply dropped. Characters can hastily doff clothing while changing, but not armor. Magic armor survives the change if it succeeds on a DC 15 Fortitude save. An afflicted character who 
is not aware of his condition remains in animal form until the next dawn. An afflicted character who is aware of his or her condition (see above) can try to resume humanoid form following a change (voluntary or involuntary) with a Control Shape check, but
 if he fails his check, he remains in animal (or hybrid) form until the following dawn.
\par }{\fs22 
\par Curing Lycanthropy
\par }{\fs20 An afflicted character who eats a sprig of belladonna (also called wolfsbane) within 1 hour of a lycanthrope\rquote s attack can attempt a DC 20 Fortitude save to shake off the affliction. If a healer administers the herb, use the character
\rquote s save bonus or the healer\rquote s Heal modifier, whichever is higher. The character gets only one chance, no matter how much belladonna is consumed. The belladonna must be reasonably fresh (picked within the last week).
\par However, fresh or not, belladonna is toxic. The character must succeed on a DC 13 Fortitude save or take 1d6 points of Strength damage. One minute later, the character must succeed on a second DC 13 save or take 
an additional 2d6 points of Strength damage. 
\par A }{\i\fs20 remove disease }{\fs20 or }{\i\fs20 heal }{\fs20 spell cast by a cleric of 12th level or higher also cures the affliction, provided the character receives the spell within three days of the lycanthrope\rquote s attack.
\par The only other way to remove the affliction is to cast }{\i\fs20 remove curse }{\fs20 or }{\i\fs20 break enchantment }{\fs20 
on the character during one of the three days of the full moon. After receiving the spell, the character must succeed on a DC 20 Will save to break the curse (the caster knows if the spell works). If the save fails, the process must be repeated. 
\par Characters undergoing this cure are often kept bound or confined in cages until the cure takes effect.
\par Only afflicted lycanthropes can be cured of lycanthropy.
\par }{
\par LYCANTHROPES AS CHARACTERS
\par }{\fs20 Becoming a lycanthrope does not change a character\rquote s favored class but usually changes alignment (see above). This alignment change may cause characters of certain classes to lose some of their class features.
\par Lycanthrope characters possess the following racial traits.
\par \emdash  +2 Wisdom. Physical abilities are increased by the animal form\rquote s ability modifiers when a lycanthrope changes to its hybrid or animal forms.
\par \emdash Size same as the base creature or the base animal form.
\par \emdash Low-light vision in any form.
\par \emdash Scent in any form.
\par \emdash Racial Hit Dice: A lycanthrope adds the Hit Dice of its animal form to its base Hit Dice for race, level, and class. These additional Hit Dice modify the lycanthrope\rquote s base attack bonus and base saving throw bonuses accordingly.
\par \emdash Racial Skills: A lycanthro
pe adds skill points for its animal Hit Dice much as if it had multiclassed into the animal type. It gains skill points equal to (2 + Int modifier, minimum 1) per Hit Die of the animal form. Any skills that appear in the animal\rquote 
s description are treated as class skills for the lycanthrope\rquote s animal levels. The lycanthrope\rquote 
s maximum skill ranks are equal to its animal form Hit Dice + its racial Hit Dice (if any) + its class levels + 3. Any racial skill adjustments of the lycanthrope\rquote s base race and its animal
 form (but not conditional adjustments) are added to its skill modifiers in any form.
\par \emdash Racial Feats: Add the animal\rquote s Hit Dice to the base character\rquote s own Hit Dice to determine how many feats the character has. All lycanthropes gain Iron Will as a bonus feat.
\par \emdash  +2 natural armor bonus in any form.
\par \emdash Special Qualities (see above): Alternate form, lycanthropic empathy, curse of lycanthropy (in animal or hybrid form only).
\par \emdash Afflicted lycanthrope: damage reduction 5/silver (in animal or hybrid form only).
\par \emdash Natural lycanthrope: damage reduction 10/silver (in animal or hybrid form only).
\par \emdash Automatic Languages: As base creature.
\par \emdash Favored Class: Same as the base creature.
\par \emdash Level adjustment: Same as the base creature +2 (afflicted) or +3 (natural).
\par 
